description: Real Madrid Club de Fútbol is a Spanish football club from Madrid. The club was founded on March 6, 1902 as Madrid Club de Fútbol. Usually the current club name is abbreviated to Real Madrid. In addition, it has some nicknames, such as Los Blancos and Los Merengues. The club plays its home games at the Estadio Santiago Bernabéu and was named by FIFA as the best football club of the 20th century.[1] Real Madrid's arch rival is FC Barcelona, ​​matches between both clubs are known as El Clásico. Real Madrid have won the Primera División thirty-five times, the Copa del Rey twenty times, the Supercopa de España thirteen times, the UEFA Super Cup five times, the UEFA Cup twice, the Intercontinental Cup three times, the FIFA Club World Cup five times and fourteen times the European Cup I / UEFA Champions League. Real Madrid is the record holder of the tournament with fourteen European Cup I / UEFA Champions League victories, ahead of the Italian AC Milan, which won the tournament seven times.
